 reasoned and documented, the argument is couched in clear prose, easily accessible to lay readers as well as to scholars.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEthics. 0aMysticism. 0aReligion and ethics. 4aPhilosophy. 4aReligion. 7aRELIGION / Mysticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978088920769140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889207691423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889207691/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles